%% Memento — capture an object's state so it can be restored later
%% (undo/redo). Rust's #[derive(Clone)] gives you the "capture" side
%% of the pattern for free; the remaining design is WHO holds the
%% history and WHAT gets snapshotted.
classDiagram
    class Editor {
        +text: String
        +cursor: usize
        +snapshot() EditorState
        +restore(EditorState)
    }
    class EditorState {
        <<Clone>>
        +text: String
        +cursor: usize
    }
    class History {
        -past: Vec~EditorState~
        -future: Vec~EditorState~
        +save(EditorState)
        +undo() Option~EditorState~
        +redo() Option~EditorState~
    }

    Editor ..> EditorState : captures snapshot
    History --> EditorState : stacks past + future
    Editor --> History : save / undo / redo

    note for EditorState "In Rust the 'memento' is just a\nClone of the relevant state.\nKeep it narrow: only the fields\nthe caretaker needs to restore."
